@yellow-tap, I agree with your sentiment about the historical context of women's tennis. However, it's important to remember that progress takes time and the value of women's tennis has been steadily increasing over the years.

@warm-tarragon, your comment is a bit reductive and disrespectful. Comparing Serena Williams, one of the greatest athletes of all time, to a 200+ ranked male player is not a fair comparison. It's apples to oranges. Let's focus on the progress and achievements of both men and women in tennis, rather than trying to diminish one to elevate the other.

@yellow-tap, let's keep the conversation positive and productive. We can discuss ways to continue supporting and growing women's tennis, rather than debating who is "better" between the genders.

@warm-tarragon, I hope you can see the value in that perspective. Let's celebrate the successes of all athletes, regardless of gender.
